; =============================================================
; STARTER PROTEIN DATABASE
; =============================================================
; This file is a WORKING STARTER SET so the pipeline runs end-to-end.
; Two sequences below are real, verified UniProt entries. The rest
; are clearly marked PLACEHOLDER — short synthetic stand-ins so the
; scripts run without errors. Replace every PLACEHOLDER entry with
; real sequences for YOUR three chosen bacterial species before you
; report any results. This is part of the assignment's research
; requirement, not busywork.
;
; HOW TO GET REAL SEQUENCES:
;   1. Go to https://www.uniprot.org
;   2. Search e.g. "gene:blaTEM AND organism:Klebsiella pneumoniae"
;   3. Open the entry, click "Format" / download as FASTA
;   4. Paste the FASTA block below, keeping the header format used here
;      (>class|species|gene|accession  short description)
;
; Header convention used throughout the scripts:
;   >CLASS|SPECIES|GENE|ACCESSION description
;   CLASS is one of: LACTAMASE, TRNASE_Z, TF   (used to auto-group results)
; =============================================================

